      "mechanism": "Defective CFTR protein impairs chloride and bicarbonate transport across epithelial cells. In airways, dehydrated mucus impairs mucociliary clearance, leading to chronic bacterial infection (Pseudomonas, Staph). In pancreas, blocked ducts cause pancreatic insufficiency.",
      "etiologies": [
        "Autosomal recessive inheritance",
        "CFTR mutations (F508del most common)",
        "Northern European ancestry highest prevalence"
      ],
      "clinical_presentation": [
        "Chronic productive cough",
